brief:
Remediate the externally validated security and production-readiness findings from .gjc/context/review-findings-validation-20260705T233915Z.md without reverting unrelated user work.

@goal: Harden AI and external-source runtime boundaries
Replace direct MockAIAdapter construction in production paths with configured runtime adapter selection, add real adapter/key handling or explicit fail-fast behavior, and stop Hermes raw item collection from silently fabricating fallback inputs when Naver credentials or API calls fail. Preserve mock usage only for explicit non-production/test paths and contract tests.

@goal: Fix cron and auth/security issues
Make Vercel Cron invocation compatible with the deployed contract, verify cron secrets from supported headers without proxy bypass gaps, remove login open redirects/token leakage, remove duplicate NextAuth exposure if unused, fail closed on missing owner email/password config, and prevent unauthenticated request logging from becoming a DoS vector.

@goal: Remove demo-data masking and tighten dependency hygiene
Stop content detail API failures from being masked as demo data for real package ids, keep deliberate demo behavior explicit, pin or remove unsafe dependency declarations, and add focused regression tests for the remediated findings.

@goal: Verify remediation end-to-end
Run focused contract/type/lint verification for the changed surfaces, perform final cleanup/review/QA gates, and checkpoint durable evidence.

